OL,7,FA legal bid for compensation by the
OL,8,Fowners of the Victoria Square
OL,9,Fapartments failed last week after it
OL,10,Fwas found to have fallen outside the
OL,11,Fterms of existing legislation, which
OL,12,Frequires claims to be made within six
OL,13,Fyears of the property's construction.
OL,14,FResidents had to leave the apartments
OL,15,Fin 2019 after a defect was identified
OL,16,Fin a structural column. They have been
OL,17,Funable to return yet are still subject
OL,18,Fto paying certain bills, such as
OL,19,Frates, for their properties.JUlster
OL,20,FGarden Villages charity owns 54 of the
OL,21,F91 apartments in Victoria Square. The
OL,22,Fremaining properties are owned by
OL,23,Findividuals.JAfter the case was struck
OL,24,Fout, Assembly members have faced calls
OL,25,Fto change the law to extend the
OL,26,Fstatutory time limit to 30 years.JThe
